President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. The nominees include Thomas Atkin for Assistant Secretary of Defense for Homeland Defense, Daniel P. Feehan for Assistant Secretary of Defense for Readiness, Marguerite Salazar for Member of the Board of Directors of the National Association of Registered Agents and Brokers, and Peter Michael McKinley for Ambassador to the Federative Republic of Brazil. The appointees include Sam W. Brown, Jr. for Member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board, Larry Mayer for Member of the Arctic Research Commission, Phyliss Craig-Taylor for Member of the President's Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities, Marian Wright Edelman for Member of the President's Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities, and Lillian Lowery for Member of the President's Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities. President Obama expressed confidence in the abilities of these individuals to tackle the important challenges facing America.